## Initial Observation

The email impersonates **Chase Bank** and informs the recipient that their bank account has been blocked due to unusual activity.

The attacker attempts to pressure the victim into clicking the **"Reactivate Your Account"** button.

This is a classic **credential phishing campaign** that relies on fear and urgency rather than exploiting software vulnerabilities.

